cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses experiments on adversarial examples generated for deep convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the robustness of machine learning models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of adversarial examples to test the robustness of machine learning models also falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the performance of different machine learning models, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the transferability of adversarial examples across different network topologies, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
